 {"id":"charmed_rust-5x5.5.3","title":"Bubbletea Program Lifecycle Conformance","description":"## Overview
Tests conformance of the Program lifecycle - initialization, run loop, update cycle, and shutdown. This is the core runtime of bubbletea.

## Lifecycle Phases

### 1. Initialization
- Model.Init() called
- Initial command executed
- First View() called

### 2. Run Loop
- Read input (keys, mouse, window size)
- Dispatch message to Update
- Execute returned command
- Call View() to render
- Repeat until Quit

### 3. Shutdown
- Quit message received
- Final cleanup
- Return final Model

## Deep-Dive: Go Program Implementation

```go
// From tea.go
func (p *Program) Run() (Model, error) {
    // Initialize
    model := p.initialModel
    cmd := model.Init()

    // Start input reader
    go p.readInput()

    // Main loop
    for {
        select {
        case msg := <-p.msgs:
            if _, ok := msg.(QuitMsg); ok {
                return model, nil
            }

            var cmd Cmd
            model, cmd = model.Update(msg)

            view := model.View()
            p.render(view)

            if cmd != nil {
                go p.executeCmd(cmd)
            }

        case <-p.ctx.Done():
            return model, p.ctx.Err()
        }
    }
}
```

